{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"11f3b220-44e0-11ed-813a-c06237dfe90a","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"02accce0-097f-44a6-9d6b-a9e3690c17db","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Hedging with Forward Contracts","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"bd8939c1-8f4b-4b6c-baa0-17a343d0bb50"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"6d05c011-94f9-4ca2-9d88-9072ab72fe3c","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Exchange rate risk naturally arises whenever transacting parties use different currencies: One of the parties will be at risk if exchange rates fluctuate. The most common method firms use to reduce the risk that results from changes in exchange rates is to hedge the transaction using ","marks":[]},{"object":"text","text":"currency forward contracts","marks":[{"type":"italic"}]},{"object":"text","text":".","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"4ecc8a15-8d45-47db-817a-931f5c6e81ac"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"321fd25b-5d4b-4e59-8e2e-d63ecaf4ebd8","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"A ","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"54cd7337-77a8-4eed-87e7-ead11b86cc58","stage":{"ref":"b6a36d52-8736-451c-9695-f20694c67597","sections":[{"ref":"b7ab1256-f910-4373-8013-2ae1530382a9","rows":[{"ref":"99e3a194-aa4c-41cb-8471-098e65baf9fc","columns":[{"ref":"78adf619-7fa3-497a-bc34-4280312ff62a","stageElements":[{"ref":"0226dce8-56c4-4b0c-a282-06d72b73c647","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"7250fe46-6562-490d-b43d-93fc428e4d7e","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"fda60975-9017-4f16-a776-e0382805dffd","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"A contract that sets a currency exchange rate, and an amount to exchange, in advance.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"currency forward contract","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"35f1de2b-9b11-47f5-b3ca-0e3fd19ca4ab"},{"object":"text","text":" is a contract that sets the exchange rate and an amount to exchange in advance. It is usually written between a firm and a bank, and it fixes a currency exchange rate for a transaction that will occur at a future date. A currency forward contract specifies (1) an exchange rate, (2) an amount of currency to exchange, and (3) a delivery date on which the exchange will take place. The exchange rate set in the contract is referred to as the ","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"2ea473b9-63ba-4fd7-a3ab-e1fac066be4e","stage":{"ref":"18c8bfdd-cc8c-47bb-bcb7-975f66a66906","sections":[{"ref":"79d277c0-4005-4a15-9bb1-69ef17d98a87","rows":[{"ref":"e4afa0ae-5967-48db-86fa-a709b09bb70b","columns":[{"ref":"52f96528-82be-4b84-bde0-480057d28524","stageElements":[{"ref":"664c8791-9d98-4b8a-a18d-e859aa033ef3","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"98327036-9803-4a5a-9af7-f11e2582b5bb","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"791216c6-096c-4243-a308-b46fff04c8fe","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The exchange rate set in a currency forward contract; it applies to an exchange that will occur in the future.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"forward exchange rate","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"18db4066-3c81-4fc4-a26a-929677c3e0c8"},{"object":"text","text":", because it applies to an exchange that will occur in the future. By entering into a currency forward contract, a firm can lock in an exchange rate in advance and reduce or eliminate its exposure to fluctuations in a currency’s value.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"d3d56c25-6279-4d4a-818a-0bb961797f62"}]}]}]},{"cssClass":"aside-group example_1","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"196f2ef5-eef6-416c-93a7-ac2bfab811e7","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Example 23.2 Using a Forward Contract to Lock in an Exchange Rate","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"69120f9e-6704-4179-9b68-1b7babfdecc6"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-three","ref":"f6ff240a-978c-49b3-a6bc-0f289f216a54","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Problem","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"30cd39c7-54d5-4dcf-bbe2-a14e5369f219"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"d6ceeb56-2f58-43c3-8e76-c7ac2ec5c65e","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Assume that in January 2009, banks were offering one-year currency forward contracts with a forward exchange rate of $1.29/€. Suppose that at that time, Manzini placed the order with Campagnolo with a price of 500,000 euros and simultaneously entered into a forward contract to purchase 500,000 euros at a forward exchange rate of $1.29/€ in January 2010. What payment would Manzini be required to make in January 2010?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"7801be2e-4213-41d2-b78d-8c5a5a134462"},{"typ