"translate(1084, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-4A\" transform=\"translate(1334, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-61\" transform=\"translate(1848, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-6E\" transform=\"translate(2348, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-75\" transform=\"translate(2904, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-61\" transform=\"translate(3460, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-72\" transform=\"translate(3960, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-79\" transform=\"translate(4352, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-A0\" transform=\"translate(4880, 0)\"></use></g><g data-mml-node=\"mn\" data-semantic-type=\"number\" data-semantic-role=\"integer\" data-semantic-font=\"normal\" data-semantic-annotation=\"clearspeak:simple\" data-semantic-id=\"11\" data-semantic-parent=\"20\" data-semantic-speech=\"2010\" transform=\"translate(20656, 0)\"><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-32\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-30\" transform=\"translate(500, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-31\" transform=\"translate(1000, 0)\"></use><use xlink:href=\"#MJX-2979-TEX-N-30\" transform=\"translate(1500, 0)\"></use></g></g></g></g></svg>"},"ref":"515ac975-9cfd-48f3-aa19-590f0714f7aa","nodes":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":"math-expression"},"ref":"4dfc43de-5b8d-4069-92a5-cc2ddf2d35f4"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"a49d5342-a7a8-4279-a80f-febf26131cc5","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Manzini would pay this amount to the bank in exchange for 500,000 euros, which are then paid to Campagnolo.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"9498e480-dafb-4927-842d-f4c017eb0e0c"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-four","ref":"7caea193-b543-4a53-9c21-1d37b461b752","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Evaluate","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"a8953c82-f043-4396-942c-1e4d4ed4c5ea"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"9c3e6f5d-3f47-46b5-b9f3-f10c41682033","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"This forward contract would have been a good deal for Manzini. Without the hedge, it would have had to exchange dollars for euros at the prevailing rate of $1.45/€, raising its cost to $725,000. However, the exchange rate could have moved the other way. If the exchange rate had fallen to $1.15/€, the forward contract would still commit Manzini to pay $1.29/€. In other words, the forward contract locks in the exchange rate and eliminates the risk—whether the movement of the exchange rate is favorable or unfavorable.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"5826798e-cd28-4e0b-9c9b-5c52b5749490"}]}]}]},{"rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"fb6b4061-96da-432a-985d-fede3820c18b","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"If the forward contract allows the importer to eliminate the risk of a stronger euro, where does the risk go? At least initially, the risk passes to the bank that has written the forward contract. Because the bank agrees to exchange dollars for euros at a fixed rate, it will experience a loss if the euro increases in value. In ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"32c9382f-a69c-45e7-849e-d146c1bbd2e6","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Example 23.2","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"a9bb05d0-44e1-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":", the bank receives only $645,000 in the forward contract, but gives up euros that are worth $725,000.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"0fc3f975-05c8-4fc1-b935-1f8c3f5d51ef"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"40b5aba1-9432-4ac4-b6f7-06d18fcdb7bf","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Why is the bank willing to bear this risk? First, the bank is much larger and has more capital than a small importer, so it can bear the risk without being in jeopardy of financial distress. More importantly, in most settings the bank will not even hold the risk. Instead, the bank will find another party willing to trade euros for dollars. By entering into a second forward contract with offsetting risk, the bank can eliminate its risk altogether.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"590299f8-679a-4bd5-b8bf-913b81a40aa7"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"441325ed-edc6-4920-97e3-b698ba922975","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"This situation is illustrated in ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"7e1e386d-8715-4a81-8bcc-34ae4fd525d5","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Figure 23.6","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"a9cabd40-44e1-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":". A U.S. importer, who must pay for goods with euros, purchases euros from the bank through a forward contract with a forward exchange rate of $1.29 per euro. This transaction locks in the importer’s cost at $645,000. Similarly, a U.S. exporter, who will receive payment in euros, uses a forward contract to sell the euros to the bank, locking in the exporter’s revenue at $645,000. The bank holds both forward contracts—the first to exchange dollars for euros and the second to exchange euros for dollars. The bank bears no exchange rate risk and earns fees from both the exporter and the importer.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"28c5098c-a635-4d4a-b9ca-5c7abb06e0ed"},{"type":"stage-element-image","config":{"url":{"$ambrosia":"aero:asset:upload","urn":"urn:aero:dbe73840-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","asset":{"urn":"urn:aero:dbe73840-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","asset":{"assetProvider":"ALFRESCO","id":"dbe73840-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","assetMediaType":"image","assetVisibility":"GLOBAL","ownerId":"e88133a0-8dc4-11eb-964e-4d7e264c9958","subscriptionId":"f0afd4d0-d2ff-11ea-9998-d57e1e28aca1","alfrescoId":"e4f66c2e-2838-4399-a861-d7a784f748e2","name":"FG_23_006.jpg","version":"2.0","lastModifiedDate":1664998399,"lastSyncDate":1665085936},"source":{"small":{"width":427,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/dbe73840-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/small/5ff9263512dc431838bc7994d441a924.jpeg","height":300},"original":{"width":854,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/dbe73840-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/medium/5ff9263512dc431838bc7994d441a924.jpeg","height":600},"medium":{"width":854,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/dbe73840-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/medium/5ff9263512dc431838bc7994d441a924.jpeg","height":600},"thumb":{"width":214,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/dbe73840-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/thumb/5ff9263512dc431838bc7994d441a924.jpeg","height":150}},"metadata":{"altText":"","workURN":"","caption":"<p>In this example, the U.S. importer and the U.S. exporter both hedge their exchange rate risk by using currency forward contracts (shown in blue). By writing offsetting contracts, the bank bears no exchange rate risk and earns a fee from each transaction.</p>","alfrescoPath":"bronte-e2e-testing-qaint/documentLibrary/BV E2E Test/[10-05-2022] Berk","originalAssetName":"FG_23_006.jpg","longDesc":"","height":"550"}}},"alt":"","caption":"<p>In this example, the U.S. importer and the U.S. exporter both hedge their exchange rate risk by using currency forward contracts (shown in blue). By writing offsetting contracts, the bank bears no exchange rate risk and earns a fee from each transaction.</p>","layout":{"captionPosition":"Below"},"credit":"","activityLabel":"Figure 23.6","activityTitle":"The Use of Currency Forwards to Eliminate Exchange Rate Risk"},"height":550,"ref":"fbd4ca1e-9f78-48b1-bfb5-24400f9c042b"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockElements":false,"learnerCurrentAttempt":1,"footer":{"buttonText":"Next","buttonIcon":"Arrow","showFooter":false,"showHistoryNavButtons":false,"previewFooter":false,"position":"Fixed to screen bottom","footerComponent":{"showFooterDropArea":"hide","width":100,"footerComponentsAlignment":"right"}},"styles":{"background":{},"stage":{"maxWidth":940,"background":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","responsive":true,"padding":{"vertical":60,"horizontal":60},"border":{"color":"rgba(224, 224, 224, 1)","radius":0,"width":0}},"elements":{"padding":{"vertical":10,"horizontal":10}},"footer":{"buttonColor":"rgba(0, 115, 202, 1)","textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","padding":10,"corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 -1px 4px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.06), 0 0 12px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"},"feedback":{"width":320,"textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 5px 47px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.15), 0 10px 20px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1), 0 7px 8px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"}},"title":"Hedging with Forward Contracts"},"assets":[{"urn":"urn:aero:dbe73840-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","asset":{"assetProvider":"ALFRESCO","id":"dbe73840-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","assetMediaType":"image","assetVisibility":"GLOBAL","ownerId":"e88133a0-8dc4-11eb-964e-4d7e264c9958","subscriptionId":"f0afd4d0-d2ff-11ea-9998-d57e1e28aca1","alfrescoId":"e4f66c2e-2838-4399-a861-d7a784f748e2","name":"FG_23_006.jpg","version":"2.0","lastModifiedDate":1664998399,"lastSyncDate":1665085936},"source":{"small":{"width":427,"url":"htt